<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    {{ template "head" . }}
    <meta name="twitter:card" content="summary">
    <meta name="twitter:site" content="@siren_tlg">
    <meta name="twitter:creator" content="@siren_tlg">
    <meta name="twitter:title" content="SIREN">
    <meta name="twitter:description" content="Bot Posts in Your Channel">
    <meta name="twitter:image" content="https://siren.chat/icons/siren-1024x1024.png">
    <meta name="image" property="og:image" content="https://siren.chat/icons/siren-1024x1024.png">
    <title>SIREN â€” Bot Posts in Your Channel</title>
</head>

<body>
{{ template "header" }}
<div class="container">
    <main>
        <h1 class="mt-4">Bot Posts in Your Channel</h1>
        <p>
            You can automatically notify your users whenever you are online in your Telegram channel or group!
        </p>

        <h4>Step 1: Add the bot to your channel or group</h4>
        <p>
            First, find the bot for your streaming platform.
            These bots talk in English.
            For bots in other languages, change the language at the bottom of the page.
        </p>

        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-lg-8 col-xl-7 table-responsive">
                <table class="table table-sm">
                    <thead>
                        <tr>
                            <th scope="col">Your site</th>
                            <th scope="col">Bot username</th>
                        </tr>
                    </thead>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Twitch</td>
                        <td class="text-nowrap overflow-auto mono">@TwitchSirenBot</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Chaturbate</td>
                        <td class="text-nowrap overflow-auto mono">@ChaturbateAlarmBot</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Stripchat</td>
                        <td class="text-nowrap overflow-auto mono">@StripchatOnlineBot</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>BongaCams</td>
                        <td class="text-nowrap overflow-auto mono">@BongaCamsOnlineBot</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>LiveJasmin</td>
                        <td class="text-nowrap overflow-auto mono">@LiveJasminSirenBot</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>CamSoda</td>
                        <td class="text-nowrap overflow-auto mono">@CamSodaSirenBot</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Flirt4Free</td>
                        <td class="text-nowrap overflow-auto mono">@Flirt4FreeSirenBot</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Streamate</td>
                        <td class="text-nowrap overflow-auto mono">@StreamateSirenBot</td>
                    </tr>
                </table>
            </div>
        </div>

        <h5 class="mt-4">For channels</h5>
        <ol>
            <li>Open your channel in Telegram</li>
            <li>Tap the channel name at the top to open channel info</li>
            <li>Tap <strong>Administrators</strong></li>
            <li>Tap <strong>Add Admin</strong></li>
            <li>Search for the bot username from the table above (e.g., <span class="mono">@ChaturbateAlarmBot</span>)</li>
            <li>Select the bot from the search results</li>
            <li>Enable these permissions: <strong>Post Messages</strong></li>
            <li>Tap the checkmark to confirm</li>
        </ol>

        <h5 class="mt-4">For groups</h5>
        <ol>
            <li>Open your group in Telegram</li>
            <li>Tap the group name at the top to open group info</li>
            <li>Tap <strong>Add Members</strong> (or <strong>Add</strong>)</li>
            <li>Search for the bot username from the table above (e.g., <span class="mono">@ChaturbateAlarmBot</span>)</li>
            <li>Select the bot from the search results to add it</li>
        </ol>

        <div class="p-3 mb-3 bg-warning">
            <strong>Important for channels:</strong> The bot must be added as an administrator with permission to post messages.
            Without admin rights, the bot cannot send notifications to your channel.
        </div>

        <h4>Step 2: Subscribe to your stream</h4>
        <p>
            Send this command in your channel or group to start receiving notifications.
        </p>

        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-lg-8 col-xl-7 table-responsive">
                <table class="table table-sm">
                    <thead>
                        <tr>
                            <th scope="col">Your site</th>
                            <th scope="col">Command</th>
                        </tr>
                    </thead>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Twitch</td>
                        <td class="text-nowrap overflow-auto mono">/add@TwitchSirenBot <strong><em>YOUR_TWITCH_CHANNEL</em></strong></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Chaturbate</td>
                        <td class="text-nowrap overflow-auto mono">/add@ChaturbateAlarmBot <strong><em>YOUR_USERNAME</em></strong></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Stripchat</td>
                        <td class="text-nowrap overflow-auto mono">/add@StripchatOnlineBot <strong><em>YOUR_USERNAME</em></strong></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>BongaCams</td>
                        <td class="text-nowrap overflow-auto mono">/add@BongaCamsOnlineBot <strong><em>YOUR_USERNAME</em></strong></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>LiveJasmin</td>
                        <td class="text-nowrap overflow-auto mono">/add@LiveJasminSirenBot <strong><em>YOUR_USERNAME</em></strong></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>CamSoda</td>
                        <td class="text-nowrap overflow-auto mono">/add@CamSodaSirenBot <strong><em>YOUR_USERNAME</em></strong></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Flirt4Free</td>
                        <td class="text-nowrap overflow-auto mono">/add@Flirt4FreeSirenBot <strong><em>YOUR_USERNAME</em></strong></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Streamate</td>
                        <td class="text-nowrap overflow-auto mono">/add@StreamateSirenBot <strong><em>YOUR_USERNAME</em></strong></td>
                    </tr>
                </table>
            </div>
        </div>
        <p>You can remove this command after the bot is set up.</p>

        <h4>Step 3 (optional): Disable offline notifications</h4>
        <p>
            By default, the bot notifies when you go offline too. To disable offline notifications, send this command.
        </p>
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-lg-9 col-xl-8 table-responsive">
                <table class="table table-sm">
                    <thead>
                        <tr>
                            <th scope="col">Your site</th>
                            <th scope="col">Command</th>
                        </tr>
                    </thead>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Twitch</td>
                        <td class="text-nowrap overflow-auto mono">/disable_offline_notifications@TwitchSirenBot</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Chaturbate</td>
                        <td class="text-nowrap overflow-auto mono">/disable_offline_notifications@ChaturbateAlarmBot</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Stripchat</td>
                        <td class="text-nowrap overflow-auto mono">/disable_offline_notifications@StripchatOnlineBot</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>BongaCams</td>
                        <td class="text-nowrap overflow-auto mono">/disable_offline_notifications@BongaCamsOnlineBot</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>LiveJasmin</td>
                        <td class="text-nowrap overflow-auto mono">/disable_offline_notifications@LiveJasminSirenBot</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>CamSoda</td>
                        <td class="text-nowrap overflow-auto mono">/disable_offline_notifications@CamSodaSirenBot</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Flirt4Free</td>
                        <td class="text-nowrap overflow-auto mono">/disable_offline_notifications@Flirt4FreeSirenBot</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Streamate</td>
                        <td class="text-nowrap overflow-auto mono">/disable_offline_notifications@StreamateSirenBot</td>
                    </tr>
                </table>
            </div>
        </div>
        <p>
            You can remove this command after the bot is set up.
            To enable offline notifications again, just replace <span class="mono">disable</span> by <span class="mono">enable</span>.
        </p>

        <h4>Step 4 (optional): Disable screenshots</h4>
        <p>
            By default, the bot sends a screenshot with each notification. To disable screenshots, send this command.
        </p>
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-lg-9 col-xl-8 table-responsive">
                <table class="table table-sm">
                    <thead>
                        <tr>
                            <th scope="col">Your site</th>
                            <th scope="col">Command</th>
                        </tr>
                    </thead>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Twitch</td>
                        <td class="text-nowrap overflow-auto mono">/disable_images@TwitchSirenBot</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Chaturbate</td>
                        <td class="text-nowrap overflow-auto mono">/disable_images@ChaturbateAlarmBot</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Stripchat</td>
                        <td class="text-nowrap overflow-auto mono">/disable_images@StripchatOnlineBot</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>BongaCams</td>
                        <td class="text-nowrap overflow-auto mono">/disable_images@BongaCamsOnlineBot</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>LiveJasmin</td>
                        <td class="text-nowrap overflow-auto mono">/disable_images@LiveJasminSirenBot</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>CamSoda</td>
                        <td class="text-nowrap overflow-auto mono">/disable_images@CamSodaSirenBot</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Flirt4Free</td>
                        <td class="text-nowrap overflow-auto mono">/disable_images@Flirt4FreeSirenBot</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Streamate</td>
                        <td class="text-nowrap overflow-auto mono">/disable_images@StreamateSirenBot</td>
                    </tr>
                </table>
            </div>
        </div>
        <p>
            You can remove this command after the bot is set up.
            To enable screenshots again, just replace <span class="mono">disable</span> by <span class="mono">enable</span>.
        </p>
    </main>
    {{ template "footer" . }}
</div>
</body>
</html>
